description:
Chemfiles is a library providing a simple and format agnostic interface
for reading and writing computational chemistry files: trajectories,
configurations, and topologies.

Independent Component Analysis. Independent Component Analysis (ICA)
using various algorithms: FastICA, Information-Maximization (Infomax),
and Joint Approximate Diagonalization of Eigenmatrices (JADE).

Functions for Kernel Smoothing Supporting Wand & Jones (1995). Functions
for kernel smoothing (and density estimation) corresponding to the book:
Wand, M.P. and Jones, M.C. (1995) "Kernel Smoothing".

Functions for Base Types and Core R and 'Tidyverse' Features. A toolbox
for working with base types, core R features like the condition system,
and core 'Tidyverse' features like tidy evaluation.

The Shapefile C Library provides the ability to write simple C programs
for reading, writing and updating (to a limited extent) ESRI Shapefiles,
and the associated attribute file (.dbf).
